Subject: Re: C90306048 - Fire at 23 Mays Street, Devonport [WW-ACTIVE.FID31=
67762]

Kia ora Grant, Thank you for your email and for confirming receipt of our l=
etter. Friday, 17 October after 2:=E2=80=8A00 pm works for me, and I=E2=80=
=99d appreciate it if testing and assessment could be scheduled accordingly=
. I also reserve my right to undertake

Kia ora Grant,

Thank you for your email and for confirming receipt of our letter.

Friday, 17 October after 2:00 pm works for me, and I=E2=80=99d appreciate i=
t if testing and assessment could be scheduled accordingly.

I also reserve my right to undertake independent testing and assessment of =
the property to ensure a full and impartial evaluation.

Having reviewed the proposed plan, I=E2=80=99m concerned the current testin=
g schedule appears incomplete. It does not include the first floor, roof ca=
vity, or the large upper deck, and the basement coverage seems partial, giv=
en the known extent of smoke, water, and chemical contamination.

I therefore request confirmation that the planned inspection and sampling w=
ill be expanded to include all levels and relevant structural areas. Altern=
atively, please confirm that Tower will meet my reasonable costs should I n=
eed to arrange independent specialists to carry out supplementary testing (=
including laboratory analysis).

Please confirm the final timing for the 17th and the revised scope of testi=
ng once available.

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella


On 8 Oct 2025, at 5:26=E2=80=AFPM, Grant Metson <Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz<m=
ailto:Grant.Metson@tower.co.nz>> wrote:

Hello Raffaella and Abigail,
Thank you for the letter received yesterday at 4:35
I am replying to acknowledge receipt of the letter, and to further acknowle=
dge that Abigail will be copied into all correspondence moving forward.
I have requested that the appointed specialists provide dates and times whe=
n they can be available.
I am proposing that the following persons complete site visit, assessing & =
testing, as a necessary pre-requisite to providing relevant reports for all=
 stakeholders to review:

Grant Metson =E2=80=93 Regional Assessing Manager
Stephen Walker =E2=80=93 Technical Building Consultant. ASURNZ.
Warwick Banks =E2=80=93 Associate Structural Engineer. CPEng
Alexandra Dalzell =E2=80=93 Forensic Scientist
Tyrell Craig =E2=80=93 Restoration Cleaning Specialist.
LBP Builder [ unconfirmed individual ] =E2=80=93 we will require the builde=
r to cut inspection holes in the wall linings so testing can be completed w=
ithin the wall cavities.

The intention is to test for smoke and chemical contamination within the wa=
ll cavities, and on the exposed surfaces downstairs. There will be a signif=
icant number of sample sites [tests] to be completed to be able to author a=
 reliable report. After initial testing is completed, our intention is to a=
pply restorative cleaning methods to targeted individual sample sites, foll=
owed by subsequent testing, post-cleaning, to provide data to measure the e=
ffectiveness of cleaning/decontamination.
All samples taken from site will require laboratory analysis before being i=
ncorporated into a report. This process may take up to 10 working days =E2=
=80=93 so we want to capture swab samples from surfaces before and after th=
e decontamination process is undertaken.

At this stage we are looking like being able to conduct this testing onsite=
, as well as CPEng site visit for assessment, on Friday October 17. Time to=
 yet be confirmed.

I am unsure from your letter attached whether Raffaella and/or other nomina=
ted parties wish to be present while this testing and assessment is being c=
onducted. Can you please confirm for me so that I can complete arrangements=
 that will suit all parties who need to be present.

Many Thanks,
Grant.

